The paper discusses the use of unrolled neural networks for image restoration tasks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The analysis of the generalization risk and its components using the Stein's Unbiased Risk Estimator (SURE) is a machine learning (cs.LG) technique. The paper also investigates the degrees-of-freedom (DOF) component of SURE, which is a concept commonly used in neural network regularization (cs.NE) and optimization (cs.IT). Finally, the paper's focus on network design and train sample size is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) more broadly.
